text: If you‚Äôre in the mood to cook something insanely delicious, this recipe won‚Äôt let you down üëá.  * Chicken Marinade:     * 800 grams chicken      * ¬º cup Greek natural yoghurt     * 1 tbsp lime juice     * 1 tsp garam masala     * 1 tsp ground turmeric     * 1 tsp sea salt     * 1/2 tsp ground white pepper * Curry paste:     * 2 tbsp oil     * 1 large onion, chopped     * 1 tsp sea salt     * 2 chillies, chopped     * 1 thumb ginger, chopped     * 4 cloves garlic, chopped     * 1/4 cup unroasted cashews * Spices:     * 4 cardamom pods      * 1/2 tsp peppercorns      * 1 tsp cumin seeds     * 5 cloves     * 1 tsp ground cumin     * ¬Ω tsp ground white pepper     * 1 tsp fenugreek seeds     * 1 tsp garam masala * To Cook:     * 1 tbsp oil     * 1 tbsp butter     * ¬Ω cup cream     * 1 cup Greek natural yoghurt To Serve: * Fresh coriander * Basmati rice * Paratha or roti Instructions: 1. Mix the chicken pieces with the yoghurt, lime juice, spices, salt and white pepper then cover and set aside for an hour or up to overnight. 2. Cook: Put the oil in a large pan on medium-high heat and add the onion and sea salt. Fry on gentle/medium heat for 5 minutes or until the onions are translucent. Add the green chilli, ginger, garlic, and cashews. Mix and fry for another 5 minutes, then transfer to a blender and whiz to combine. Add ¬æ cup of water, and blend to a smooth paste then set to the side. 3. Spices: Put the whole spices in a dry frying pan and cook over medium heat for a few minutes until fragrant. Cool, then put the spices in a spice grinder and grind to a fine powder. 4. To Cook: Melt the oil and butter together and add the onion-cashew paste. Cook on medium heat for 5 minutes until the paste thickens. Add the marinated chicken pieces, the freshly ground spices, garam masala, cumin and white pepper. Mix and cook on medium heat for 10 minutes. Reduce the heat to low, then add the yoghurt. Cook on low heat for around 5 minutes while stirring continuously until the mixture separates. Add the water and cream and cook on low heat for 10-12 minutes until the chicken is tender.  Serve & enjoy! This beautiful recipe is via the Dish magazine. #easyrecipe #easyrecipes #easyrecipesathome #curry #chickencurry #recipe #dinnerrecipe #dinneridea #dinnerinspo #momtok #sahmtok #nztiktok

text: To celebrate their 90th Birthday, @Watties_NZ is launching a cookbook and is calling for Kiwi's to submit their family favourite Wattie's recipes! I‚Äôm entering my Nan‚Äôs Rustic Beetroot & Caramelised Onion Galette. You can enter too for a chance to have your recipe featured here: https://watties90thbirthday.foodinaminute.co.nz/. Ingredients Dough: 150g all-purpose flour 1/2 tsp salt 115g unsalted butter, cold and cut into small cubes 60ml ice water Filling: 2 tablespoons olive oil 3 red onions, thinly sliced 1 bag Wattie's Free Flow frozen spinach 4 tbsp balsamic vinegar 1 tbsp brown sugar 1 can Wattie's tinned Sliced Beetroots, drained¬† 1 egg (beaten) 1/2 cup walnuts, chopped & toasted 100g feta cheese, crumbled 2 tbsp fresh thyme 2 tbsp honey (or hot honey for a kick) Method - In a food processor, combine the flour and salt. Pulse to mix. - Add cold, cubed butter to the flour mixture. Pulse. - With the processor running, gradually add the ice water, one tablespoon at a time, until the dough begins to come together and form clumps. - Turn the dough out onto floured surface & gather it into a ball. Flatten into a disc, wrap it in plastic wrap, and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes. - In a frying pan, heat olive oil over medium heat. - Add the sliced onion and saut√©. - Stir in the balsamic vinegar and sugar, and saut√© on low until caramelised.¬† - Add the spinach, cook for another 3-4 minutes until the spinach is heated through. - Season with salt and pepper. - Remove from heat and set aside to cool. - Preheat your oven to 190¬∞C and line a baking sheet with parchment paper. - On a lightly floured surface, roll out the chilled dough into a rough circle about 30 cm in diameter. - Transfer the rolled-out dough to the prepared baking sheet. - Spread the cooled onion and spinach mixture evenly over the dough, leaving a border around the edges. - Arrange the sliced beetroot over the top. - Sprinkle the walnuts and feta on top. - Drizzle the honey over the entire filling. - Gently fold the edges of the dough over the filling, pleating as necessary to create a rustic edge.  - Brush the folded edges of the dough with egg wash. - Bake the galette for 35-40 minutes on a lower rack, or until the crust is golden brown and the filling is bubbly and heated through. - Remove from the oven, top with thyme and let it cool for a few minutes before slicing and serving. #easyrecipe #easyrecipes #galette #familymealideas #familyfood #familyrecipe #recipes #recipesoftiktok #dinnerideas #momtok #sahmtok #homemade #fromscratch #nztiktok

text: Replying to @Sarah Parsons Easy Cheesy Beef Lasagna üëá (save for later). Ingredients: * 1 large onion, finely chopped * 3 cloves garlic, minced * 1 red capsicum (bell pepper), chopped * 1 medium carrot, grated * 1 medium courgette (zucchini), grated * Handful of mushrooms, sliced * 1 kg woolworths beef mince * 2 tbsp smoked paprika * 2 tbsp ground cumin * Salt and pepper, to taste * 1 can (400g) chopped tomatoes Cheese Sauce ingredients: * 2 tbsp butter  * 2 tbsp plain flour * 300ml milk (about 1 ¬º cups) * 100g grated cheese  * Salt and pepper, to taste * @Woolworths New Zealand fresh lasagna sheets * handful grated mozzarella cheese (for topping) Meat sauce:     * Heat a large pan over medium heat and add a drizzle of oil.     * Saut√© chopped onion & minced garlic until translucent      * Add chopped bell pepper, grated carrot, grated courgette, and sliced mushrooms     * Saut√© the vegetables together until just cooked     * Add the beef mince & season with smoked paprika, cumin, salt, and pepper, stir until browned     * Stir in the chopped tomatoes and simmer until reduced.  Cheese sauce:     * In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat.     * Add the flour and stir constantly to form a roux.     * Gradually whisk in the milk, continuing to stir until the sauce thickens and is smooth.     * Remove from heat and stir in the grated cheese.     * Season with pepper to taste. Assemble the Lasagne:     * Preheat your oven to 200¬∞C      * Spread a thin layer of the meat and vegetable sauce on the bottom of a large baking dish.     * Cover in cheese sauce.     * Place a layer of fresh lasagna sheets on top.     * Repeat.     * Sprinkle the grated mozzarella cheese evenly over the top layer.     * Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake for 15 minutes.     * Remove the foil and bake for an additional 15-20 minutes until the mozzarella on top is golden and bubbly. #easyrecipe #easyrecipes #lasagna #lasagne #lasagnarecipe #familyfriendly #kidfriendly #kidfriendlyrecipe #familydinner #familyrecipe #recipeideas #comfortfood #momtok #sahmtok #nztiktok
